Step 4: Connect via VS Code
Refresh the Remote Explorer pane in VS Code.
Find the compute node you just added to the list (e.g., pax046.pax.tufts.edu).
Hover over the node name and click the Connect in Current Window icon (or right-click and select it).
Wait for the connection to establish. You should see the green SSH indicator in the bottom-left corner of VS Code confirm the active connection to your node.
Step 5: Load class Modules
Make sure you have loaded the class module

module load class/default
module load cs137/2026spring
