Step 6: Open Your Working Directory
Now that VS Code is running directly on your allocated compute node, you can open your class folder.

Click Open Folder in the VS Code Explorer pane (or go to File > Open Folder).
Type in the absolute path to your specific CS137 student directory:
/cluster/tufts/c26sp1cs0137/<your_utln>

Click OK. VS Code will reload into that directory, and you are ready to code!